pub.citation: Lindqvist, C. and V. A. Albert. 2002. ORIGIN OF THE HAWAIIAN ENDEMIC MINTS WITHIN NORTH AMERICAN STACHYS (LAMIACEAE). American Journal of Botany 89(10): 1709-1724.

pmmd.notes: Fig. 5. Phylogeny of Stachys sensu lato based on total available evidence. A phylogram of one of four most-parsimonious trees based on combined rbcL, trnL intron, and 5S-NTS sequence data is shown. Numbers of unambiguous nucleotide substitutions are shown above branches, and parsimony jackknife values above 50% are shown below branches. Branches that collapse in the strict consensus tree are shown with stippled lines. Numbers following taxon names refer to individual accessions.
